<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="245" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1058</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 12, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to the last paragraph of your
                            cable of February 5, noon, in reference to a United States war vessel
                            being stationed off the north coast of Santo Domingo until after the
                            election, the Department informs you that it is not deemed expedient
                            that a vessel be now sent for duty at any one point on the north coast
                            of that republic.</p>
                        <p>The U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Wheeling</hi> will be stationed at Cape
                            Haitien for some weeks, and may be ordered to proceed to Puerto Plata
                            should the situation there demand her presence.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>